      "body": "```suggestion\r\ncurl --fail -L \"https://github.com/koalaman/shellcheck/releases/download/${SHELLCHECK_VERSION}/shellcheck-${SHELLCHECK_VERSION}.linux.$(uname -m).tar.xz\" | \\\r\n```\r\n\r\nnit: Instead of `--silent` it could make more sense to `--fail`. Otherwise, an http error will silently be ignored. E.g.\r\n\r\n```\r\nsh-5.3$ curl --fail -L \"https://github.com/koalaman/shellcheck/releases/download/${SHELLCHECK_VERSION}/shellcheck-${SHELLCHECK_VERSION}.linux.$(uname -m).tar.xz\" \r\ncurl: (22) The requested URL returned error: 404\r\nsh-5.3$ echo $?\r\n22\r\nsh-5.3$ curl -L \"https://github.com/koalaman/shellcheck/releases/download/${SHELLCHECK_VERSION}/shellcheck-${SHELLCHECK_VERSION}.linux.$(uname -m).tar.xz\" \r\nNot Foundsh-5.3$ echo $?\r\n0\r\n",
